**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Extracts `xml` payload from the request. If the content type is not XML, an `http:ClientError` is returned.
  
  
  
**Returns** `(xml|error)`   
- The `xml` payload or `http:ClientError` in case of errors

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Checks whether the client expects a `100-continue` response.
  
  
  
**Returns** `boolean`   
- Returns true if the client expects a `100-continue` response

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Sets a `ByteChannel` as the payload.
  
**Params**  
- `io:ReadableByteChannel` payload: A `ByteChannel` through which the message payload can be read  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the payload. Set this to override the default `content-type`
                header value(Defaultable)  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the payload. Set this to override the default `content-type`
                header value

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Gets the request payload as a `byte[]`.
  
  
  
**Returns** `(byte[]|error)`   
- The byte[] representation of the message payload or `http:ClientError` in case of errors

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Extracts `json` payload from the request. If the content type is not JSON, an `http:ClientError` is returned.
  
  
  
**Returns** `(json|error)`   
- The `json` payload or `http:ClientError` in case of errors

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Gets the query param value associated with the given key.
  
**Params**  
- `string` key: Represents the query param key  
  
**Returns** `(string|())`   
- Returns the query param value associated with the given key as a string. If multiple param values are  
present, then the first value is returned. Nil is returned if no key is found.
**Package:** _ballerina/http_

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Extracts `text` payload from the request. If the content type is not of type text, an `http:ClientError` is returned.
  
  
  
**Returns** `(string|error)`   
- The `text` payload or `http:ClientError` in case of errors

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Create a new `Entity` and link it with the request.
  
  
  
**Returns** `mime:Entity`   
- Newly created `Entity` that has been set to the request

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
  
  
  
**Returns** `mime:Entity`

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Returns the value of the specified header. If the specified header key maps to multiple values, the first of
these values is returned.
  
**Params**  
- `string` headerName: The header name  
  
**Returns** `string`   
- The first header value for the specified header name. An exception is thrown if no header is found. Use  
`hasHeader()` beforehand to check the existence of header.

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Sets the provided `Entity` to the request.
  
**Params**  
- `mime:Entity` e: The `Entity` to be set to the request

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Sets the specified header to the request. If a mapping already exists for the specified header key, the existing
header value is replaced with the specified header value.
  
**Params**  
- `string` headerName: The header name  
- `string` headerValue: The header value

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Gets the request payload as a `ByteChannel` except in the case of multiparts. To retrieve multiparts, use
`getBodyParts()`.
  
  
  
**Returns** `(io:ReadableByteChannel|error)`   
- A byte channel from which the message payload can be read or `http:ClientError` in case of errors

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Sets a `string` as the payload.
  
**Params**  
- `string` payload: The `string` payload  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the payload. Set this to override the default `content-type` header value
                for `string`(Defaultable)  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the payload. Set this to override the default `content-type` header value
                for `string`

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Sets the `content-type` header to the request.
  
**Params**  
- `string` contentType: Content type value to be set as the `content-type` header  
  
**Returns** `(()|error)`   
- Nil if successful, error in case of invalid content-type

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Sets the request payload. Note that any string value is set as `text/plain`. To send a JSON-compatible string,
set the content-type header to `application/json` or use the `setJsonPayload` method instead.
  
**Params**  
- `(string|xml|json|byte[]|io:ReadableByteChannel|mime:Entity[])` payload: Payload can be of type `string`, `xml`, `json`, `byte[]`, `ByteChannel`, or `Entity[]` (i.e., a set
of body parts).
**Package:** _ballerina/http_

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Gets all the query param values associated with the given key.
  
**Params**  
- `string` key: Represents the query param key  
  
**Returns** `(string[]|())`   
- Returns all the query param values associated with the given key as a `string[]`. Nil is returned if no key  
is found.

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Sets the content of the specified file as the entity body of the request.
  
**Params**  
- `string` filePath: Path to the file to be set as the payload  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the specified file. Set this to override the default `content-type`
                header value(Defaultable)  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the specified file. Set this to override the default `content-type`
                header value

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Removes all the headers from the request.

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Adds the specified header to the request. Existing header values are not replaced.
  
**Params**  
- `string` headerName: The header name  
- `string` headerValue: The header value

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Set multiparts as the payload.
  
**Params**  
- `mime:Entity[]` bodyParts: The entities which make up the message body  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the top level message. Set this to override the default
                `content-type` header value(Defaultable)  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the top level message. Set this to override the default
                `content-type` header value

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Gets the `Entity` associated with the request.
  
  
  
**Returns** `(mime:Entity|error)`   
- The `Entity` of the request. An `http:ClientError` is returned, if entity construction fails

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Checks whether the requested header key exists in the header map.
  
**Params**  
- `string` headerName: The header name  
  
**Returns** `boolean`   
- Returns true if the specified header key exists

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Sets an `xml` as the payload.
  
**Params**  
- `xml` payload: The `xml` payload  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the payload. Set this to override the default `content-type` header value
                for `xml`(Defaultable)  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the payload. Set this to override the default `content-type` header value
                for `xml`

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Sets a `json` as the payload.
  
**Params**  
- `json` payload: The `json` payload  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the payload. Set this to override the default `content-type` header value
                for `json`(Defaultable)  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the payload. Set this to override the default `content-type` header value
                for `json`

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Removes the specified header from the request.
  
**Params**  
- `string` key: The header name

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Check whether the entity body is present.
  
  
  
**Returns** `boolean`   
- a boolean indicating entity body availability

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Gets all the names of the headers of the request.
  
  
  
**Returns** `string[]`   
- An array of all the header names

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Gets the query parameters of the request as a map consisting of a string array.
  
  
  
**Returns** `map<string[]>`   
- String array map of the query params

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Extracts body parts from the request. If the content type is not a composite media type, an error
is returned.  
  
  
**Returns** `(mime:Entity[]|error)`   
- Returns the body parts as an array of entities or an `http:ClientError` if there were any errors in  
constructing the body parts from the request

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Gets the type of the payload of the request (i.e: the `content-type` header value).
  
  
  
**Returns** `string`   
- Returns the `content-type` header value as a string

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Gets the matrix parameters of the request.
  
**Params**  
- `string` path: Path to the location of matrix parameters  
  
**Returns** `map<any>`   
- A map of matrix parameters which can be found for the given path

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Gets the form parameters from the HTTP request as a `map` when content type is application/x-www-form-urlencoded.
  
  
  
**Returns** `(map<string>|error)`   
- The map of form params or `http:ClientError` in case of errors

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Sets a `byte[]` as the payload.
  
**Params**  
- `byte[]` payload: The `byte[]` payload  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the payload. Set this to override the default `content-type` header value
                for `byte[]`(Defaultable)  
- `string` contentType: The content type of the payload. Set this to override the default `content-type` header value
                for `byte[]`

**Package:** _ballerina/http_  
  
Gets all the header values to which the specified header key maps to.
  
**Params**  
- `string` headerName: The header name  
  
**Returns** `string[]`   
- The header values the specified header key maps to. An exception is thrown if no header is found. Use  
`hasHeader()` beforehand to check the existence of header.
